<%- include('partials/header', { title }) %>
<section class="hero hero-home">
  <div class="hero-copy">
    <span class="eyebrow">AI-powered attendance</span>
    <h1>Scan faces, record sessions, and keep every student accounted for.</h1>
    <p>Attendra keeps attendance fast, traceable, and organized with one command center for rosters, scans, alerts, and reports.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href="/attendance/face">Start face scan</a>
      <a class="button ghost" href="/attendance/manual">Manual entry</a>
      <a class="button ghost" href="/students/new">Add student</a>
    </div>
    <div class="stats-strip">
      <div class="stats-item">
        <span class="metric-label">Students</span>
        <strong><%= studentCount %></strong>
      </div>
      <div class="stats-item">
        <span class="metric-label">Faces enrolled</span>
        <strong><%= enrolledCount %></strong>
      </div>
      <div class="stats-item">
        <span class="metric-label">Sessions</span>
        <strong><%= sessionCount %></strong>
      </div>
      <div class="stats-item">
        <span class="metric-label">Records</span>
        <strong><%= recordCount %></strong>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-stack">
    <div class="hero-panel">
      <div class="hero-metric">
        <div class="metric-label">Face coverage</div>
        <div class="metric-value"><%= studentCount ? Math.round((enrolledCount / studentCount) * 100) : 0 %>%</div>
        <p>Enroll faces before the first session so scan mode can identify students immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-metric">
        <div class="metric-label">Workflow</div>
        <div class="metric-value">3 steps</div>
        <p>Enroll, scan, then review records and analytics from the same interface.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-grid">
  <article class="card feature-card">
    <span class="eyebrow">Roster control</span>
    <h2>Manage students in one place</h2>
    <p>Edit IDs, contact details, and face enrollment status without leaving the dashboard.</p>
    <a class="text-link" href="/students">Open students</a>
  </article>
  <article class="card feature-card">
    <span class="eyebrow">Face scan</span>
    <h2>Recognize students in real time</h2>
    <p>Use the camera flow to mark students present and keep the rest absent by default.</p>
    <a class="text-link" href="/attendance/face">Open face attendance</a>
  </article>
  <article class="card feature-card">
    <span class="eyebrow">Manual entry</span>
    <h2>Record attendance for any date</h2>
    <p>Backfill sessions or correct records with a quick, predictable form.</p>
    <a class="text-link" href="/attendance/manual">Open manual form</a>
  </article>
  <article class="card feature-card">
    <span class="eyebrow">Analytics</span>
    <h2>See attendance risk at a glance</h2>
    <p>Spot students below the cutoff and export clean records for review.</p>
    <a class="text-link" href="/analytics">View analytics</a>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <div class="section-head">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2>From enrollment to attendance</h2>
    </div>
    <a class="button ghost" href="/settings/notifications">Review settings</a>
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-grid">
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <span class="timeline-index">01</span>
      <h3>Enroll faces</h3>
      <p>Capture a clear front-facing image for each student so the model can build a descriptor.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <span class="timeline-index">02</span>
      <h3>Scan a session</h3>
      <p>Open face attendance, start the camera, and scan each student one by one.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <span class="timeline-index">03</span>
      <h3>Review outcomes</h3>
      <p>Check the record list and analytics to see which students were marked present.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
